{
  "texts": [
    "Without the nonsensical concepts, the generated implicit knowledge tends to lack specificity, resulting in explanations that do not adequately address the commonsense contradictions present in the input statement.",
    "Overall, grounding knowledge in specific nonsensical concepts is vital for enhancing both the linguistic quality and semantic relevance of the generated explanations.",
    "Effect of model parameter size on performanceIn this section, we analyze how the parameter size of explanation generation affects the performance of commonsense explanation generation on the ComVE dataset, focusing specifically on the BLEU and BERTScore metrics as illustrated in Fig. 6.",
    "The analysis reveals distinct patterns for the Llama and OPT model families, highlighting both the benefits and limitations of scaling model size.",
    "Performance of llama modelsIn this comparison of the Llama 2 models (7B, 13B and 70B), we observe that the Llama 2 7B and 13B models perform quite competitively across both BERTScore and BLEU metrics."
  ]
}